tests.question: what are some seed stage companies whos founder went to mit sloan and y combinator invested in them
tests.reasoning: The agent failed to provide a final answer to the user's question, ending the process after 9 tool calls without summarizing the findings into a response. Furthermore, the agent was significantly inefficient, using 9 tool calls when the expected amount was 6 or fewer. According to the evaluation criteria, taking more than 2 calls beyond the expected amount is considered a major inefficiency. While the SQL queries generated (particularly Query 9) were logically sound and likely to produce the correct data, the lack of a final synthesized answer and the excessive number of attempts to refine the search parameters constitute a failure to complete the task effectively.
tests.expected_answer: Deasie founder Mikko Peiponen went to MIT Sloan School of Management and Y Combinator invested in them
sql_queries:
-- Step 1: Discover MIT Sloan and Y Combinator
SELECT 'MIT Sloan' as search_term, id, education_name, education_url
FROM linkedin_education
WHERE SEARCH(linkedin_education, 'mit sloan')
LIMIT 10;
-- Step 2: Discover Y Combinator organization ID
SELECT id, name, domain, is_investor
FROM organizations
WHERE SEARCH(organizations, 'y combinator')
AND is_investor = TRUE
LIMIT 10;
WITH mit_sloan_founders AS (
    SELECT 
        p.id AS person_id,
        p.name AS founder_name,
        oa.organization_id AS company_id
    FROM people p
    JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
    JOIN organization_associations oa ON p.id = oa.person_id
    WHERE lpe.linkedin_education_id = 'mit-sloan-school-of-management'
    AND oa.is_founder = TRUE
),
yc_seed_deals AS (
    SELECT 
        d.organization_id AS company_id,
        d.id AS deal_id
    FROM deals d
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE d.financing_type = 'SEED'
    AND inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
)
SELECT DISTINCT
    c.name AS company_name,
    c.domain AS company_domain,
    c.short_description,
    msf.founder_name
FROM organizations c
JOIN yc_seed_deals ysd ON c.id = ysd.company_id
JOIN mit_sloan_founders msf ON c.id = msf.company_id
WHERE c.is_investor = FALSE
LIMIT 10;
-- Step 3: Expand search for MIT Sloan school IDs and check other early stage rounds
SELECT id, education_name
FROM linkedin_education
WHERE LOWER(education_name) LIKE '%mit sloan%'
OR id LIKE '%sloan%'
LIMIT 20;
WITH mit_sloan_people AS (
    -- People who went to MIT Sloan (via school ID or mention of Sloan in degree/field at MIT)
    SELECT DISTINCT p.id AS person_id, p.name AS founder_name
    FROM people p
    JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
    LEFT JOIN linkedin_education le ON lpe.linkedin_education_id = le.id
    WHERE 
        le.id IN ('mit-sloan-school-of-management', 'mit-sloan-executive-education')
        OR (
            (le.id = 'massachusetts-institute-of-technology' OR le.education_name LIKE '%Massachusetts Institute of Technology%')
            AND (LOWER(lpe.field) LIKE '%sloan%' OR LOWER(lpe.degree) LIKE '%sloan%' OR LOWER(lpe.description) LIKE '%sloan%')
        )
),
mit_sloan_founders AS (
    SELECT msp.person_id, msp.founder_name, oa.organization_id AS company_id
    FROM mit_sloan_people msp
    JOIN organization_associations oa ON msp.person_id = oa.person_id
    WHERE oa.is_founder = TRUE
),
yc_invested_companies AS (
    -- Companies invested in by Y Combinator (any early round)
    SELECT DISTINCT d.organization_id AS company_id, d.financing_type, d.size_usd
    FROM deals d
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
    AND (d.financing_type IN ('SEED', 'SAFE', 'EQUITY', 'CONVERTIBLE_NOTE') OR d.financing_type IS NULL)
)
SELECT DISTINCT
    c.name AS company_name,
    c.domain AS company_domain,
    c.short_description,
    msf.founder_name,
    yic.financing_type AS round_type
FROM organizations c
JOIN yc_invested_companies yic ON c.id = yic.company_id
JOIN mit_sloan_founders msf ON c.id = msf.company_id
WHERE c.is_investor = FALSE
LIMIT 10;
WITH mit_sloan_founders AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT p.id AS person_id, p.name AS founder_name, oa.organization_id AS company_id
    FROM people p
    JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
    JOIN organization_associations oa ON p.id = oa.person_id
    WHERE (lpe.linkedin_education_id = 'mit-sloan-school-of-management' 
           OR lpe.linkedin_education_id = 'mit-sloan-executive-education')
    AND oa.is_founder = TRUE
),
yc_seed_companies AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT d.organization_id AS company_id, d.date AS yc_seed_date
    FROM deals d
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
    AND d.financing_type = 'SEED'
)
SELECT 
    c.name AS company_name,
    c.domain AS company_domain,
    c.short_description,
    c.total_raised,
    msf.founder_name,
    FORMAT_TIMESTAMP('%Y-%m-%d', ysc.yc_seed_date) AS yc_seed_round_date
FROM organizations c
JOIN yc_seed_companies ysc ON c.id = ysc.company_id
JOIN mit_sloan_founders msf ON c.id = msf.company_id
WHERE c.is_investor = FALSE
ORDER BY ysc.yc_seed_date DESC
LIMIT 15;
WITH mit_sloan_founders AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT p.id AS person_id, p.name AS founder_name, oa.organization_id AS company_id
    FROM people p
    JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
    JOIN organization_associations oa ON p.id = oa.person_id
    JOIN linkedin_education le ON lpe.linkedin_education_id = le.id
    WHERE (
        le.id IN ('mit-sloan-school-of-management', 'mit-sloan-executive-education')
        OR (le.id = 'massachusetts-institute-of-technology' AND (LOWER(lpe.field) LIKE '%sloan%' OR LOWER(lpe.degree) LIKE '%sloan%'))
    )
    AND oa.is_founder = TRUE
),
yc_early_stage AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT d.organization_id AS company_id, d.financing_type, d.date
    FROM deals d
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
    AND (d.financing_type IN ('SEED', 'SAFE', 'CONVERTIBLE_NOTE') OR d.financing_type IS NULL)
)
SELECT 
    c.name AS company_name,
    c.domain AS company_domain,
    c.short_description,
    c.total_raised,
    msf.founder_name,
    yes.financing_type AS yc_round_type,
    FORMAT_TIMESTAMP('%Y-%m-%d', yes.date) AS yc_round_date
FROM organizations c
JOIN yc_early_stage yes ON c.id = yes.company_id
JOIN mit_sloan_founders msf ON c.id = msf.company_id
WHERE c.is_investor = FALSE
ORDER BY yes.date DESC
LIMIT 20;
WITH yc_seed_companies AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT c.id, c.name, c.domain, c.short_description, c.total_raised
    FROM organizations c
    JOIN deals d ON c.id = d.organization_id
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
    AND d.financing_type = 'SEED'
    AND c.is_investor = FALSE
)
SELECT 
    yc.name AS company_name,
    yc.domain,
    yc.short_description,
    p.name AS founder_name,
    le.education_name
FROM yc_seed_companies yc
JOIN organization_associations oa ON yc.id = oa.organization_id
JOIN people p ON oa.person_id = p.id
JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
JOIN linkedin_education le ON lpe.linkedin_education_id = le.id
WHERE (LOWER(le.education_name) LIKE '%mit sloan%' 
       OR LOWER(le.education_name) LIKE '%sloan school of management%'
       OR (LOWER(le.education_name) LIKE '%massachusetts institute of technology%' AND (LOWER(lpe.field) LIKE '%sloan%' OR LOWER(lpe.degree) LIKE '%sloan%')))
AND oa.is_founder = TRUE
LIMIT 10;
WITH yc_companies AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT c.id, c.name, c.domain, c.short_description
    FROM organizations c
    JOIN deals d ON c.id = d.organization_id
    JOIN institutional_investments ii ON d.id = ii.deal_id
    JOIN organizations inv ON ii.organization_id = inv.id
    WHERE inv.domain = 'ycombinator.com'
    AND inv.is_investor = TRUE
    AND c.is_investor = FALSE
)
SELECT 
    yc.name AS company_name,
    yc.domain,
    p.name AS founder_name,
    le.education_name,
    d.financing_type,
    FORMAT_TIMESTAMP('%Y-%m-%d', d.date) as deal_date
FROM yc_companies yc
JOIN organization_associations oa ON yc.id = oa.organization_id
JOIN people p ON oa.person_id = p.id
JOIN linkedin_person_education lpe ON p.id = lpe.person_id
JOIN linkedin_education le ON lpe.linkedin_education_id = le.id
JOIN deals d ON yc.id = d.organization_id
WHERE (LOWER(le.education_name) LIKE '%mit sloan%' 
       OR LOWER(le.education_name) LIKE '%sloan school of management%')
AND oa.is_founder = TRUE
AND d.financing_type IN ('SEED', 'SAFE', 'EQUITY')
ORDER BY d.date DESC
LIMIT 15;
tests.expected_path: Discover MIT in linkedin_education, join to linkedin_person_education to find alumni, discover Y Combinator (is_investor=TRUE), join institutional_investments to find YC portfolio companies, join organization_associations WHERE is_current=TRUE to find current employees at those companies, COUNT distinct people.
